        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-27T09:59:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think we want to encourage the use of std::shared_ptr\u003c\u003e in our code base, since it\u0027s very inefficient. I\u0027d prefer using a std::unique_ptr\u003c\u003e instead if you insist on providing convenience pointer wrappers.\n\nI know EmuGL only implemented the equivalent of std::shared_ptr\u003c\u003e in the past, but there is no reason to pursue this anymore, especially in its public interface, instead of the actual implementation.",
      "revId": "57d1994b2207c53a8d3eb097f419cc7aef1e6fcc",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a8594975_6e11379c",
        "filename": "distrib/android-emugl/host/include/OpenglRender/IRenderLib.h",
