      },
      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-27T23:06:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In this very place it\u0027s really not needed at all, but for the rest of them I think it\u0027s necessary.\nRenderer/RenderingChannel/RenderThread need to be able to call into each other, e.g. to get the data, force stop etc. shared/weak pointers simplify the lifetime management in this multi-threaded configuration tremendously.",
      "parentUuid": "68d6710e_e07622f6",
      "revId": "57d1994b2207c53a8d3eb097f419cc7aef1e6fcc",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
