        "id": 1078773
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-28T21:15:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since C++11 STL containers support move semantics, returning them by value doesn\u0027t necessarily mean executing extra work. \n\nI.e.\nstd::vector\u003cint\u003e result(0,1,2);\nreturn result;\n\nwill not result in any extraneous copying, since a move constructor (rather than copy ctor) will be invoked and the internal state of \"result\" will be transferred to the new object",
      "parentUuid": "889d6572_913e7c18",
      "revId": "57d1994b2207c53a8d3eb097f419cc7aef1e6fcc",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
